cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with constraint satisfaction problems arising from query evaluation problems in database theory, which suggests that cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses hypergraph measures and their influence on the complexity of the problem, which falls under the scope of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions fixed-parameter tractability, which is a topic in cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of hypergraph measures and their relationship with tractability also suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are possible sub-categories.
